	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Also, re: cheap firewall: I recommend the Linksys WRT54GS units if you're looking for a firewall + NAT solution.  They're generally inexpensive, run Linux, and have a slew of firmwares available out there from the public (I use HyperWRT).
<br />
<br />If money is a big stickler, and you'd prefer to use an actual PC for a NAT+fw unit (vs. an embedded device), you might consider SmoothWall.  I'm told the thing is *wonderful*, and from what little I've read about it, it seems to be so.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


